Deployment
------------------
why we have to use Deployment?
if you want to do auto scale or rollback to pervious version these is the possible way to do that
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: mydeploy
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: frontend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: mycont
          image: shaikmustafa/dm
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80
--------------------------------------------------------
-> kubectl scale deploy mydeploy --replicas=4
->kubectl set image deploy mydeploy cont1=shaikmustafa/dm
------------------------------------------
i want to rollout to previous version?
->kubectl rollout history deploy mydeploy--> it will previous version
->i want deploy version 1
->kubectl rollout undo deploy mydeploy --to-revision=1
->kubectl rollout status deploy mydeploy
if you want to ad any annotaions
->kubectl annotate deploy mydeploy kubernetes.io/change-cause='roll backto version 1" --overwrite

